  "contenu": [
    {
      "id": "ebcb1672-94d9-49a2-b3fc-69dd52416e82",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $E = \\mathcal{C}([0,1],\\R)$ muni du produit scalaire usuel et, pour $f \\in E$ :\n$\\varphi(f) =  \\int_{t=0}^{1/2} f(t)\\,d t$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(E = \\mathcal{C}([0,1],\\R)\\)</span> muni du produit scalaire usuel et, pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f \\in E\\)</span> : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\varphi(f) =  \\int_{t=0}^{1/2} f(t)\\,d t\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "08962f1d-9be0-4b7f-9fa7-9c3fafbc0749",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $\\varphi$ est continue.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\varphi\\)</span> est continue.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ae721343-20c5-421e-a90c-7ab8ba96f73b",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $H = \\mathrm{Ker}\\varphi$ est fermé.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(H = \\mathrm{Ker}\\varphi\\)</span> est fermé.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "b03fe08c-c649-4e09-acfc-7e606a11524f",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $H^\\bot = \\{0\\}$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(H^\\bot = \\{0\\}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ed0fa75c-b5a7-4211-9d89-e3c31c679e7c",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $g \\in H^\\bot$ non nulle. Les formes linéaires :\n             $f  \\mapsto  \\int_{0}^{1/2} f$ et $f  \\mapsto  \\int_0^1 fg$ sont\n             nulles sur $H$, donc proportionnelles, ce qui est impossible\n             pour $g$ continue.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(g \\in H^\\bot\\)</span> non nulle. Les formes linéaires : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f  \\mapsto  \\int_{0}^{1/2} f\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f  \\mapsto  \\int_0^1 fg\\)</span> sont nulles sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(H\\)</span>, donc proportionnelles, ce qui est impossible pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(g\\)</span> continue.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
}